# Line-ending policy for NemesisBot Rust sources.
#
# Force LF for *.rs regardless of core.autocrlf. The repo already stores *.rs
# blobs as LF (core.autocrlf=true strips CRLF on commit); this attribute makes
# checkouts produce LF working trees too, so rustfmt output (LF) and git agree
# and the "LF will be replaced by CRLF" churn for Rust files disappears.
#
# Scoped to *.rs ONLY — .bat/.ps1/.sh/.json/.toml/etc. intentionally keep their
# current (CRLF) line endings here. Normalizing those is a separate, larger
# change. (Aside: scripts/build-linux.sh is currently CRLF, which can break
# execution under Linux bash — worth fixing on its own, not via this file.)
*.rs text eol=lf
